prompt_template:
Create a {ASPECT_RATIO} raster poster in the "Y2K Streetwear Sticker Collage Style" visual system.

Subject: {SUBJECT}
Action: {SUBJECT_ACTION}
Prop/Product: {PRODUCT_OR_PROP}
Location: {LOCATION}
Background: {BACKGROUND_ELEMENTS}
Main text: {MAIN_TEXT}
Secondary text: {SECONDARY_TEXT}
Accent symbol: {ACCENT_SYMBOL}
Wardrobe/styling: {WARDROBE_STYLE}
Style fidelity anchors: {STYLE_FIDELITY_ANCHORS}
Source content to avoid: {SOURCE_CONTENT_TO_AVOID}

Apply these style rules as literal visual direction:
- Composition: dense social-poster photo collage with one oversized cutout-photo subject pushed off center, a smaller tilted inset panel or reflective crop, oversized foreground sticker props, a speech bubble or badge, and a huge top, bottom, or corner headline.
- Perspective: casual wide-angle street-camera perspective with shallow urban depth, slightly tilted diagonals, cropped edges, and close foreground objects.
- Typography: inflated Y2K comic headline letters, thick black outer keyline, white separator stroke, mixed red, blue, yellow, black, and white fills, warped baseline, plus smaller slanted sticker labels.
- Color: saturated caution yellow, cobalt blue, teal green, punch red, deep black, and clean white over gray pavement, dark glass, asphalt, and muted metal.
- Photo treatment: photoreal street-image base, hard cutout edges, glossy oversharpened contrast, controlled social-poster compression texture, clean sticker outlines, no vector-only look.
- Graphic elements: sticker props, speech bubble with symbolic marks, badge buttons, warning-label shapes, clipped photo objects, and tilted frames.

Important content rule: match the style fidelity anchors first, then change the source content. Use the new subject, new scene, new props, new headline, and new story details. Do not recreate anything listed in the source content to avoid.
